<ptxt>Remove the shift solenoid valve DSL.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C113970E02" width="2.775699831in" height="2.775699831in"/>
</figure>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard resistance</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.07in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.06in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt>
<ptxt>20°C (68°F)</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Solenoid Connector (DSL) - Solenoid Body (DSL)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>11 to 13 Ω</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the positive (+) lead to the terminal of the solenoid connector, and the negative (-) lead to the solenoid body.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>The solenoid valve makes an operating sound.</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
</test1>
